<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:239735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pseudomyrmex lizeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lizeri">Pseudomyrmex lizeri</taxonomicName>
is known from a pair of localities in eastern Paraguay where it is locally sympatric with the common 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:35775" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pseudomyrmex flavidulus (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidulus">P. flavidulus</taxonomicName>
. There is no reason to consider the two forms conspecific. In Paraguay, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:239735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pseudomyrmex lizeri" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lizeri">Pseudomyrmex lizeri</taxonomicName>
is a noticeably larger ant than 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:35775" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pseudomyrmex flavidulus (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidulus">P. flavidulus</taxonomicName>
and has a disproportionately broader head. I have not examined the type material of this species, but Phil Ward identified the Paraguayan specimens and concurs with a change in status for 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:152064" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pseudomyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Pseudomyrmex flavidulus lizeri (Santschi)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="flavidulus" subSpecies="lizeri">P. lizeri</taxonomicName>
(Ward, pers comm.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
